# Adaptive Query Execution (AQE)

## The problem it fixes

- Pre-3.0 Catalyst decided **upfront** from *estimated* stats — and estimates are often wrong
- **AQE re-optimizes at runtime**, after each shuffle, using the *real* partition stats it just measured

## Three things it does

- **Coalesce partitions** — merge many tiny post-shuffle partitions into right-sized ones (less task-startup overhead)
- **Switch join strategy** — promote sort-merge → broadcast when a side turns out small
- **Handle skew** — split oversized partitions so one task doesn't stall the stage

## Mental model

- The **same optimizer**, given a second chance at **each stage boundary** with facts, not guesses
- On by default since **Spark 3.2**
